
                                            The party says they will not tolerate greed and corruption in the organisation and anyone found to be guilty of this would be dealt with accordingly.
                                         JOHANNESBURG – The Congress of the People (Cope) has suspended their Limpopo chairperson Patrick Sikhutshi for alleged misappropriation of funds. Sikhutshi has been suspended with immediate effect pending an investigation into the allegations. The party says they will not tolerate greed and corruption in the organisation and anyone found to be guilty of this would be dealt with accordingly. Cope spokesperson Glacier Nkwashu says: “When launching our party in 2008 and in all our election manifestos we pledged that we will run government with selflessness, accountability, and transparency. We promised that our leaders will be reliable, accountable and incorruptible.”